cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for image super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a content adaptive resampler (CAR) which generates image resampling kernels, making it likely to also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of a differentiable upscaling module also suggests the possibility of multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) categories.
